166
00:14:54,680 --> 00:14:56,360
I want to make a living in another way.

167
00:14:57,280 --> 00:14:58,976
When your parents are released
from prison,

168
00:14:59,400 --> 00:15:00,920
if they can't regain their position,

169
00:15:01,440 --> 00:15:03,560
I want to rent a bigger yard
to settle everyone.

170
00:15:04,640 --> 00:15:06,520
The business on the boat is good,

171
00:15:07,360 --> 00:15:09,160
but the actual profit is rather thin.

172
00:15:09,520 --> 00:15:11,320
It may be difficult
to make a living by then.

173
00:15:12,520 --> 00:15:13,320
People

174
00:15:13,760 --> 00:15:15,240
must keep moving forward.

175
00:15:16,800 --> 00:15:18,080
Have you thought of me?

176
00:15:22,600 --> 00:15:23,680
Of course, I have.

177
00:15:24,960 --> 00:15:27,640
But I don't know
what kind of things you are doing.

178
00:15:28,840 --> 00:15:30,360
Imperial matters are secretive.

179
00:15:31,320 --> 00:15:32,400
Who can tell

180
00:15:32,520 --> 00:15:34,000
how things will go?

181
00:15:37,920 --> 00:15:39,808
I only hope
you can extricate yourself safely.

182
00:15:40,320 --> 00:15:41,640
That's the best.

183
00:15:42,800 --> 00:15:44,120
(I still can't tell her I'm)

184
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:45,720
(helping the Crown Prince.)

